   "text": "Corrections per Jun-2026 verification (DECISIONS.md) are shown in GREEN across panels A-J.  Below: every symbol/term in plain English.",
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "Corrections per Jun-2026 verification (DECISIONS.md) are shown in GREEN across panels A-J.  Below: every symbol/term in plain English.",
   "lineHeight": 1.25,
   "baseline": 20
  },
  {
   "type": "text",
   "version": 1,
   "versionNonce": 900000150,
   "isDeleted": false,
   "id": "glossK_col1",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 2,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 0,
   "opacity": 100,
   "angle": 0,
   "x": 80,
   "y": 1868,
   "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
   "backgroundColor": "transparent",
   "width": 348,
   "height": 312,
   "seed": 900000151,
   "groupIds": [],
   "frameId": null,
   "roundness": null,
   "boundElements": [],
   "updated": 1735000000001,
   "link": null,
   "locked": false,
   "fontSize": 10,
   "fontFamily": 2,
   "text": "MODEL & MATH SYMBOLS\n• p - the market’s \"% chance\"; price of a YES share ~\n   probability\n• log-odds X=ln(p/(1-p)) - a stretched ruler for\n   probability: 0-1 -> -inf..+inf so it can’t pass 0/1\n   (like decibels for sound)\n• sigma - belief-volatility = how jumpy opinion is; the\n   price’s wobble\n• sigma^2 - variance = the wobble as energy (sigma\n   squared)\n• EWMA - running avg weighting recent data more (your mood\n   = mostly this week)\n• b (beta) - EWMA memory knob 0-1: high=smooth/slow,\n   low=twitchy/fast\n• mu - drift = the slow steady trend (a river’s gentle\n   current)\n• dW - diffusion = random jitter of normal news (a leaf on\n   ripples)\n• J.dN - jumps = sudden big moves; dN= happened? 0/1, J=\n   how big (firework vs jitter)\n• lambda - jump intensity = how OFTEN jumps fire\n• lambda* - exit threshold: if lambda passes it, pull\n   orders\n• E[loss|jump] - average damage IF a jump hits (insurance\n   expected payout)",
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "MODEL & MATH SYMBOLS\n• p - the market’s \"% chance\"; price of a YES share ~\n   probability\n• log-odds X=ln(p/(1-p)) - a stretched ruler for\n   probability: 0-1 -> -inf..+inf so it can’t pass 0/1\n   (like decibels for sound)\n• sigma - belief-volatility = how jumpy opinion is; the\n   price’s wobble\n• sigma^2 - variance = the wobble as energy (sigma\n   squared)\n• EWMA - running avg weighting recent data more (your mood\n   = mostly this week)\n• b (beta) - EWMA memory knob 0-1: high=smooth/slow,\n   low=twitchy/fast\n• mu - drift = the slow steady trend (a river’s gentle\n   current)\n• dW - diffusion = random jitter of normal news (a leaf on\n   ripples)\n• J.dN - jumps = sudden big moves; dN= happened? 0/1, J=\n   how big (firework vs jitter)\n• lambda - jump intensity = how OFTEN jumps fire\n• lambda* - exit threshold: if lambda passes it, pull\n   orders\n• E[loss|jump] - average damage IF a jump hits (insurance\n   expected payout)",
   "lineHeight": 1.25,
   "baseline": 20
  },
  {
   "type": "text",
   "version": 1,
   "versionNonce": 900000161,
   "isDeleted": false,
   "id": "glossK_col2",
   "fillStyle": "solid",
   "strokeWidth": 2,
   "strokeStyle": "solid",
   "roughness": 0,
   "opacity": 100,
   "angle": 0,
   "x": 480,
   "y": 1868,
   "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
   "backgroundColor": "transparent",
   "width": 348,
   "height": 225,
   "seed": 900000162,
   "groupIds": [],
   "frameId": null,
   "roundness": null,
   "boundElements": [],
   "updated": 1735000000001,
   "link": null,
   "locked": false,
   "fontSize": 10,
   "fontFamily": 2,
   "text": "ESTIMATOR & STATS TERMS\n• hazard / logistic - model giving a probability of an\n   event (P(dispute soon)); the S-curve classifier\n• calibration - are your %s honest? \"30%\" should happen\n   ~30% (a good weather forecaster)\n• structural signals - facts about the market (proposer,\n   size, category), NOT the rule wording\n• shrinkage / prior - too little data -> lean on the\n   category average (a new restaurant judged by its\n   cuisine)\n• depth-weighted mid - fair middle weighted by size on\n   each side (crowd by loudness, not last whisper)\n• favorite-longshot tilt - favorites slightly underpriced,\n   longshots overpriced; light fix\n• no lookahead - never use future info at time t (grading\n   without the later answer key)\n• wash trading - fake self-trades that move price &\n   pollute sigma",
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "ESTIMATOR & STATS TERMS\n• hazard / logistic - model giving a probability of an\n   event (P(dispute soon)); the S-curve classifier\n• calibration - are your %s honest? \"30%\" should happen\n   ~30% (a good weather forecaster)\n• structural signals - facts about the market (proposer,\n   size, category), NOT the rule wording\n• shrinkage / prior - too little data -> lean on the\n   category average (a new restaurant judged by its\n   cuisine)\n• depth-weighted mid - fair middle weighted by size on\n   each side (crowd by loudness, not last whisper)\n• favorite-longshot tilt - favorites slightly underpriced,\n   longshots overpriced; light fix\n• no lookahead - never use future info at time t (grading\n   without the later answer key)\n• wash trading - fake self-trades that move price &\n   pollute sigma",
   "lineHeight": 1.25,
   "baseline": 20
  },
  {
   "type": "text",
   "version": 1,
   "versionNonce": 900000172,
   "isDeleted": false,
