   "locked": false,
   "fontSize": 10,
   "fontFamily": 2,
   "text": "RATES, RESULT & HONESTY\n• base-rate DENOMINATOR — how many markets resolved per\n   category (from HF)\n• dispute NUMERATOR — how many disputed — from keyless-RPC +\n   NegRisk map (HF has 0)\n• Wilson CI — an error bar for a rate from few events; with\n   few disputes it stays honestly wide\n• control-matched replay — compare disputed markets vs\n   similar non-disputed \"controls\" so the result isn’t just\n   market-mix\n• adversarial review — a multi-agent self-audit that found &\n   fixed 12 issues (e.g. a hardcoded flag that faked the\n   first result)\n• power_calc — with ~1% disputes, few events → read the\n   ablation as \"underpowered\", not \"no edge\"\n• dossier — the reproducible dataset audit (1.17B fills,\n   992,485 resolved) behind DATASET.md",
   "textAlign": "left",
   "verticalAlign": "top",
   "containerId": null,
   "originalText": "RATES, RESULT & HONESTY\n• base-rate DENOMINATOR — how many markets resolved per\n   category (from HF)\n• dispute NUMERATOR — how many disputed — from keyless-RPC +\n   NegRisk map (HF has 0)\n• Wilson CI — an error bar for a rate from few events; with\n   few disputes it stays honestly wide\n• control-matched replay — compare disputed markets vs\n   similar non-disputed \"controls\" so the result isn’t just\n   market-mix\n• adversarial review — a multi-agent self-audit that found &\n   fixed 12 issues (e.g. a hardcoded flag that faked the\n   first result)\n• power_calc — with ~1% disputes, few events → read the\n   ablation as \"underpowered\", not \"no edge\"\n• dossier — the reproducible dataset audit (1.17B fills,\n   992,485 resolved) behind DATASET.md",
